# 2p_grapple_bone — client. Equips Grappling Hook on the secondary,
# swaps to it, aims at the stationary host's chest, fires. The hook
# head flies across the platform and lands on the host's body — the
# bone-hit branch in projectile_step.
#
# What proves Phase 4: on the host side, the `grapple_attach`
# SHOT_LOG line carries `lag_comp=N` with N > 0 because the firer
# (mech=1) has `input_view_tick` set by server_handle_input. Without
# Phase 4, lag_comp=0 even though mech=1's view tick was non-zero —
# the projectile_step bone test ran current-time regardless.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/grapple_bone_client
network connect 127.0.0.1:24191
name ClientB
loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Grappling Hook" Light Standard

spawn_at 2100 1080
aim 2300 1080

# Round-start arrives ~tick 130 (shotmode's 1s auto-start +
# handshake settle); 2p_combat fires its first weapon at tick 280
# for the same reason. Wait for the mech to spawn before swapping
# slots, then fire a tick later.
at 250 tap swap
at 280 tap fire
at 320 shot t320_in_flight
at 380 shot t380_attached
at 500 shot t500_swinging
at 700 end
